HEADWORD: Mopboard
<hw>Mop"board`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Carp.)</fld>
<def>A narrow board nailed against the wall of a room next to the floor;
skirting board; baseboard. See <er>Baseboard</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

